Mapas en R (OpenStreetMap data with R)

Ejercicio basado en: 1. Accessing OpenStreetMap data with R by Dominic Royé 2. Streetmaps by ggplot2tutor

Links: 1. https://dominicroye.github.io/en/2018/accessing-openstreetmap-data-with-r/ 2. https://ggplot2tutor.com/tutorials/streetmaps

Haciendo la estructura de la consulta 

# buildeing a query / haciendo la estructura de la consulta
consulta <- getbb("Quito") %>%  # crea un cuadro delimitador de la consulta
      opq() %>%  #funcion principal
       add_osm_feature("shop", "anime")
anime <- osmdata_sf(consulta)

Haciendo un mapa de las calles de Quito

Haciendo la estructura de la consulta 

# buildeing a query / haciendo la estructura de la consulta
consulta_calles <- getbb("Quito") %>%  # crea un cuadro delimitador de la consulta
      opq() %>%  #funcion principal
       add_osm_feature(key = "highway", 
                  value = c("motorway", "primary", 
                            "secondary", "tertiary"))
calles <- osmdata_sf(consulta_calles)
calles
Object of class 'osmdata' with:
                 $bbox : -0.3801641,-78.6723274,-0.0601641,-78.3523274
        $overpass_call : The call submitted to the overpass API
                 $meta : metadata including timestamp and version numbers
           $osm_points : 'sf' Simple Features Collection with 28992 points
            $osm_lines : 'sf' Simple Features Collection with 5870 linestrings
         $osm_polygons : 'sf' Simple Features Collection with 30 polygons
       $osm_multilines : NULL
    $osm_multipolygons : NULL
calles_pequeñas <- getbb("Quito")%>%
  opq()%>%
  add_osm_feature(key = "highway", 
                  value = c("residential", "living_street",
                            "unclassified",
                            "service", "footway")) %>%
  osmdata_sf()

rio <- getbb("Quito")%>%
  opq()%>%
  add_osm_feature(key = "waterway", value = "river") %>%
  osmdata_sf()
ggplot() +
  geom_sf(data = calles$osm_lines,
          inherit.aes = FALSE,
          color = "#ffbe7f",
          
          size = .4,
          alpha = .8) + geom_sf(data = calles_pequeñas$osm_lines,
          inherit.aes = FALSE,
          color = "#ffbe7f",
          
          size = .2,
          alpha = .8) + geom_sf(data = rio$osm_lines,
          inherit.aes = FALSE,
          color = "#ffbe7f",
          
          size = .4,
          alpha = .8)+ 
  coord_sf(xlim = c(-78.65,-78.34), ylim = c(-0.45,0),expand = FALSE) + theme_void()  +
  theme(
    plot.background = element_rect(fill = "#282828")
  )
